-----------------------------------------------------------------------
REQUIREMENTS
-----------------------------------------------------------------------
* Perl 5.6.1 or later
* Apache 1.3.x or 2.x with mod_perl
* A DBMS (so far, tested with MySQL only)

* Make sure you have the following Perl Modules installed:

DBI
Class::DBI
HTML::Mason
Apache::Session
Apache::DBI
DBIx::DBSchema
DBIx::DataSource
SNMP (from Net-SNMP package, not Net::SNMP)
Net::IP
NetAddr::IP
SiteControl (see http://whizzo.uoregon.edu/public/releases/), which needs:
	Apache::AuthCookie
	Carp::Assert
	
----------------------------------------------------------------------
SCHEMA CHANGES
----------------------------------------------------------------------

If there are schema changes between your current installation and the 
version you plan to install, it is highly recommended that you:

  * Review README.  If there are changes, it will be documented in 
    this file.
  * Back up your existing database.  mysqldump is one option for MySQL 
    installations.
  * Review contrib/updateschema.data to see what changes will occur.
  * Run updateschema.pl with the appropriate options.

updateschema.pl will manage the schema changes for you.  After you run
this script, you will have to restart httpd.

----------------------------------------------------------------------
INSTALLING THE PACKAGE
----------------------------------------------------------------------

From the main directory do:

% make install 

where you may want to pass, or change in the makefile, one or more of

PREFIX=YOUR-PREFIX (default /usr/local/netdot) 
APACHEUSER=USER-YOUR-APACHE-RUNS-AS (default apache)
APACHEGROUP=GROUP-YOUR-APACHE-RUNS-AS (default apache)


% make installdb

where you may want to change the values of

DB_NETDOT_USER=(default netdot_user)
DB_NETDOT_PASS=(default netdot_pass)

in *bin/Makefile*.

----------------------------------------------------------------------
APACHE CONFIGURATION
----------------------------------------------------------------------
* Either use the supplied template etc/netdot_apache2_radius.conf, which 
  relies on Radius for authentication.  (For apache2)

  or

* Use the template etc/netdot_apache12_htpasswd.conf -- which relies on 
  an htpasswd file for authentication -- and create the file 
  YOUR-PREFIX/htpasswd.users and add username/passwords to authenticate 
  accesss to the Netdot pages.  (For apache or apache2)

* Edit mason.pl to your needs.  
  Pay attention to the Apache2-only directives, and also the paths.
